                                            CredentialRefreshListener refreshListener)

        Returns TokensResponse containing access and refresh tokens. Also sets the returned tokens into this client instance to be used for requests.

                                             throws TokenResponseException,
                                                    java.io.IOException
        Returns TokensResponse containing access and refresh tokens. Also sets the returned tokens into this client instance to be used for requests.

        Throws:

      • setTokenResponse

        public void setTokenResponse(TokenResponse tokenResponse,
                             CredentialRefreshListener refreshListener)
                      throws java.io.IOException
        Sets up access and refresh tokens to be used for requests with this client. If refresh token is provided, it will be used to automatically refresh access tokens when requests are made if they are expired or will expire soon (in less than 1 minute).
        Parameters:
        tokenResponse - TokenResponse contains access and refresh tokens and access token expiry time
        refreshListener - CredentialRefreshListener which is called when tokens are automatically refreshed
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
